<div>
  <p>
    We provide a single package containing the server and the client tools.
    For a standard server setup, download the <strong>Server</strong> package
    and run the installer.
  </p>
  <p>
    The <strong>Client Tools</strong> package only contain the tools, like
    arangosh and arangodump, but not the server. Use this in case you are already running
    ArangoDB on a different machine and want to connect to that server from a
    client machine.
  </p>
  <p>
    As an alternative there is a <strong>Zip</strong> package containing the
    server and client tools, which can be unpacked in any location.
  </p>
  <hr/>
  <p><strong>NSIS</strong> packages</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="@DOWNLOAD_LINK@/Windows/@WINDOWS_NAME_SERVER_EXE@">Server</a><br>
      (@WINDOWS_SIZE_SERVER_EXE@ MByte, SHA256 @WINDOWS_SHA256_SERVER_EXE@)
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="@DOWNLOAD_LINK@/Windows/@WINDOWS_NAME_CLIENT_EXE@">Client Tools</a></li>
      (@WINDOWS_SIZE_CLIENT_EXE@ MByte, SHA256 @WINDOWS_SHA256_CLIENT_EXE@)
    </li>
  </ul>
  <hr/>
  <p><strong>Zip</strong> packages</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="@DOWNLOAD_LINK@/Windows/@WINDOWS_NAME_SERVER_ZIP@">Server</a><br>
      (@WINDOWS_SIZE_SERVER_ZIP@ MByte, SHA256 @WINDOWS_SHA256_SERVER_ZIP@)
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>
